# Zigo / Eduspire Software Blueprint

Build Zigo as a mobile-first verified education media platform.

Global slogan: The Smart, Verified, and Gamified Social Feed for Education.
Concept: Eduspire / EduAg, a verified education media network.

## 1. Technical Stack

- Platform: mobile-first web app / PWA.
- Frontend default: React/Next.js.
- Backend default: Supabase.
- Alternative backend: Node.js/Express only when custom server logic is necessary.
- Database: PostgreSQL.
- Authorization: Supabase/PostgreSQL Row Level Security. Never rely on frontend-only permission checks.

Core philosophy: turn TikTok/Instagram-like feed habits into a useful educational habit through verified education content, questions, micro learning, and gamification. The product should feel like LinkedIn + Quora + gamified micro learning + short-form learning video, not a generic social network.

## 2. PostgreSQL Schema Contract

The implementation must preserve these core tables and relationships. Supabase projects should use `auth.users(id)` as the source auth identity and mirror profile data in `public.users`.

```sql
create type user_role as enum ('teacher', 'parent', 'student');

create table users (
  id uuid primary key default gen_random_uuid(),
  email varchar(255) unique not null,
  full_name varchar(100) not null,
  role user_role not null,
  is_verified boolean default false,
  avatar_assets jsonb default '{"hat": null, "suit": null, "pet": null}',
  total_points int default 0,
  created_at timestamp default current_timestamp
);

create table education_areas (
  id serial primary key,
  area_name varchar(100) unique not null,
  age_group varchar(50)
);

create table user_interests (
  user_id uuid references users(id) on delete cascade,
  area_id int references education_areas(id) on delete cascade,
  primary key (user_id, area_id)
);

create table posts (
  id uuid primary key default gen_random_uuid(),
  teacher_id uuid references users(id) on delete cascade,
  title varchar(255),
  content text,
  media_url varchar(255),
  area_id int references education_areas(id),
  created_at timestamp default current_timestamp
);

create table questions (
  id uuid primary key default gen_random_uuid(),
  author_id uuid references users(id) on delete cascade,
  area_id int references education_areas(id),
  title varchar(255) not null,
  description text not null,
  is_resolved boolean default false,
  created_at timestamp default current_timestamp
);

create table answers (
  id uuid primary key default gen_random_uuid(),
  question_id uuid references questions(id) on delete cascade,
  teacher_id uuid references users(id) on delete cascade,
  content text not null,
  is_approved_by_parent boolean default false,
  created_at timestamp default current_timestamp
);
```

## 3. Role And Authorization Rules

User roles are exactly `teacher`, `parent`, and `student`.

- `teacher`: verified education content creator.
- `parent`: supervision, analytics, questions, child progress, and reward approval.
- `student`: gamified learner with micro learning, quizzes, duels, points, Zigo Crystals, and avatar customization.

Hard rules:

- Only `role = 'teacher'` and `is_verified = true` users can create posts.
- Teachers can create posts only in education areas assigned to them through `user_interests`.
- Teachers can answer questions only in assigned areas.
- Parents and students can never create posts.
- Parents and students can create questions only in selected areas.
- Parents and students can read posts only when `posts.area_id` matches their `user_interests.area_id`.
- Students cannot send direct messages.
- Student-visible text must pass profanity and cyberbullying moderation before display.

## 4. Match-Feed Algorithm

The main feed invariant is:

> A post appears in a user's feed only when `posts.area_id` exists in that user's `user_interests`.

Use this Supabase-style query shape for the personalized feed:

```ts
const getPersonalizedFeed = async (userId: string) => {
  const { data, error } = await supabase
    .from("posts")
    .select(`
      id,
      title,
      content,
      media_url,
      created_at,
      users:teacher_id (
        full_name,
        is_verified
      )
    `)
    .in(
      "area_id",
      supabase.from("user_interests").select("area_id").eq("user_id", userId),
    );

  if (error) throw error;
  return data;
};
```

## 5. UI/UX Rules

Entry can use a Netflix-style profile selection model under one account.

Parent profile:

- Serious, calm, analytics-focused.
- LinkedIn/Quora-like visual tone.
- Shows child progress, time spent, teacher answers, selected areas, and reward approvals.

Student profile:

- Fully gamified, colorful, and mobile-first.
- Playful, game-like energy.
- Shows avatar, level, league, crystal balance, streaks, micro videos, quizzes, and duels.

Teacher profile:

- Verified creator dashboard.
- Shows assigned education areas, post composer, question inbox, and answer history.

## 6. Positive Social Media Engine

- No student-to-student DM.
- Use a safety wall for comments and open text.
- Add regex-based profanity filtering first; design the moderation layer so AI moderation can be added later.
- Award points only for verified learning actions.
- Watching a verified one-minute micro lesson grants `+10` education points.
- Completing a mini quiz grants `+10` education points.
- Winning a duel grants a configurable reward.
- Store earned points in `users.total_points`.
- Store avatar equipment in `users.avatar_assets`.
- Build a Kumbara Store for hats, capes, suits, pets, frames, and parent-approved real-world rewards such as book coupons.

## 7. Initial Implementation Prompt

When implementing from scratch, start with this instruction:

```text
Yukarıdaki PostgreSQL şemasını, Supabase Row Level Security kurallarını ve Zigo iş kurallarını temel alarak mobil öncelikli bir eğitim platformu geliştir.

Öğretmenler sadece `role = 'teacher'` ve `is_verified = true` ise, ayrıca sadece kendi `user_interests` uzmanlık alanlarında post paylaşabilmeli ve gelen soruları cevaplayabilmeli.

Veliler ve öğrenciler sadece seçtikleri alanlardaki öğretmen gönderilerini görebilmeli.

Öğrenciler için `total_points`, Zigo Kristali ve `avatar_assets` tabanlı mini avatar özelleştirme sistemi oluştur.

Veli ve öğrenci asla bağımsız içerik postu paylaşamasın; sadece soru sorabilsin.

İlk olarak Supabase entegrasyonunu, veritabanı bağlantı fonksiyonlarını, typed data access helpers, Match-Feed sorgusunu, role-aware auth profil yüklemeyi ve temel backend/API rotalarını oluştur.
```
